metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, Orpheus is more complex than the typical song, having above average scores in Chord Complexity, Melodic Complexity, Chord-Melody Tension and Chord Progression Novelty.
key_conclusion: Orpheus has sections analyzed in the following keys: E Major,  and C Major.  Click on the linked cheat sheets for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: Synced piano tempo; also, this piece uses a pedal point on E for the first six measures, but Hookpad does not currently support slash chords so I just had to use the lowest chord tone
